article.headline: N.J. Tech 65, Texas-Pan American 63
article.story: EDINBURG, Texas -- Jheryl Wilson's basket at the buzzer in overtime gave New Jersey Tech a 65-63 victory at Texas-Pan American Saturday night. Wilson rebounded a missed shot by Isiah Wilkerson and scored, making the Highlanders winners for the sixth straight game. Wilkerson had 18 points and 11 rebounds for NJIT (13-12, 7-1) and Arjun Ohri added 11 points. The Highlanders rallied from a 15-point deficit early in the second half. Matt Mierzycki had 11 points and 11 rebounds for the Broncs (4-23, 1-9), including two free throws with 1 second to play to tie the game at 57. Brandon Provost led UTPA with 13 points and Ruben Cabrera had 10 points.
